Commentary.Commentary: We are back to begin India's first innings! The England players make their way out to the middle followed by Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill. James Anderson will start with the ball. 12 overs remain in the day.

So England have once again failed with the bat and find themselves chasing this game already. Their bowlers will once again have to do a top-class job to keep their side in the hunt in this game. The Indian openers will come and their first task would be to see off the day without much damage. Can England strike a couple of blows and put the hosts under pressure or will India end with a perfect day?

What a stunning performance yet again by the hosts with the ball! Once again it is the local boy, Axar Patel who will grab the headlines! He has not been a very welcoming host but a gem for his team. The man has taken Test cricket like a duck to water and has finished with yet another 4-fer. Ashwin too was in the thick of action. Though he started the day off slowly, not picking a wicket in the first two sessions. He did the damage in the third and finished with 3. Siraj bowled very well and asked a lot of questions and deserved his 2. Sundar too bagged one for himself. Ishant did not look at his usual best and went wicketless but he still did not leak runs.

After winning the toss and opting to bat, the story of the series continued. The England batters struggled to get going with both the openers falling early to Axar Patel. Root too did not last long. Bairstow and Stokes tried to steady the ship but their 48-run stand was cut short. Stokes' fifty gave some hope but that was cut short as well soon after. Pope and Lawrence showed some fight but none of them could capitalize on the starts they got and wickets at regular intervals meant England were bundled out for 205!

Another superb bowling display from India and another lacklustre show with the willow by the English batters. They once again fell to the same trap they have fallen in the series since the second Test. The Axar-Ashwin trap! We are all set to begin the final session of Day 1! The Indian players stride out to the middle, followed by Dan Lawrence and Ollie Pope. Mohammed Siraj will begin with the ball. 34 overs left in the day's play.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Good utilization of resources from Kohli. He has rotated the bowlers well. Siraj started the session well and gave his side the early breakthrough, bowling his heart out in the heat. The bowlers kept things tight and surprisingly it is a session where both Axar and Ashwin have gone wicketless. Just when it looked like England were getting a grip, Sundar got rid of the dangerous southpaw. Overall a good session for India. They will try to wrap up the tourists by the end of the day's play. England, on the other hand, have selected an extra batsman for this game and will hope Pope and Lawrence can build on their starts. The final session of the day will be a crucial one in this Test. Make sure you join us for that at 1430 local (0900 GMT).

The session did not start off well for the tourists as they lost Bairstow early. Stokes was looking good out in the middle and steadied the ship with fifty but unfortunately could not carry on. Pope and Lawrence are still out in the middle and have stitched a 23-run stand so far. Ollie Pope has fought hard for his 21 and will look to make it count. Lawrence has looked solid as well.

So England have dominated the second hour of the first session but if they are to stay alive in this game, they will need to do that for the whole of the second session. India will be looking to get rid of this partnership early in the second session and get a stronghold in this game. Can Bairstow and Stokes continue their fight or will India come roaring back? Join us for the second session at 1210 local (0640 GMT) to find out.

Good bowling display from India so far. Once again it was Axar who has done majority of the damage. The left-arm spinner was introduced early and that decision reaped rewards as he got the better of the English openers. Siraj too looked good and got one. Ishant was unable to find his lines and lengths consistently. Ashwin did not bowl much and is just at the start of his spell. Another enjoyable session for the hosts in this Test.

After opting to bat, England once again failed to get a steady start. They lost both the openers, Sibley and Crawley to Axar. Skipper, Joe Root too failed to make an impact. The hosts were struggling at 30/3 but Stokes and Bairstow have done well since then. The pair have added 44 runs and are looking good out in the middle. The job though is nowhere close to being done as the tourists will need this pair to bat for a long period and put them in a commanding position.

A solid end to the session for England but still it was India's session. A good session, which had wickets, runs, and also some chatter. 3 wickets in the first session and the hosts will be happy with how things have panned out.

We are all set to begin! The Indian players stride out to the middle, followed by Dom Sibley and Zak Crawley. Ishant Sharma will start with the ball for the hosts.

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma, Shubman Gill, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Rishabh Pant (WK), Washington Sundar, Axar Patel, Ravichandran Ashwin, Ishant Sharma, Mohammed Siraj (IN PLACE OF JASPRIT BUMRAH).

England (Playing XI) - Dom Sibley, Zak Crawley, Jonny Bairstow, Joe Root (C), Ben Stokes, Ollie Pope, Ben Foakes (WK), Dan Lawrence (IN PLACE OF JOFRA ARCHER), Dom Bess (IN PLACE OF STUART BROAD), Jack Leach, James Anderson.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper, says that they would have batted first as well. Goes onto say that it has been amazing and they have come up the ranks very well. States that people love watching them play and it is good to lead this team. Adds that England is a quality team and they have put pressure on them in the past. Tells that they have to be at their top of the game. Informs that they have made just one change as Jasprit Bumrah has gone home and Mohammed Siraj replaces him.

Joe Root, the England skipper, says that they would like to bat first. Adds that they are progressing as a side in the last couple of years and hopes to end the winter on a high with a win. States that whenever you have a tough couple of games, they have to trust their own ability and back themselves. Informs that they have made a couple of changes as Dom Bess and Dan Lawrence come in for Stuart Broad and Jofra Archer.
Toss - It is time for the all-important toss and both Virat Kohli and Joe Root are in the middle. Up goes the coin and it lands in favour of England, They have elected to bat first.

Pitch report - Deep Dasgupta is there for the pitch report. He says that there is little more moisture on this pitch. He is joined by Ajit Agarkar. Agarkar says that there is lot less grass at the Reliance End and this End is likely to spin more. Deep says that the moisture will go away. Agarkar hopes that the footmarks will hold.

England, on the other hand, would be desperate to level the series. They have been annihilated in the last couple of Test matches but they would hope to come back stronger in this game and try their level best to win the match. They made a tactical blunder in the last match by playing just a single spinner but that might change in this game as Dom Bess is likely to play. Whom will he replace? We will have to wait and watch. What about the team changes for India? They will be without Jasprit Bumrah for this Test and it seems like Umesh Yadav will get the nod over Mohammed Siraj to replace Bumrah. Will there be any other changes?

India are the favourites going into this game. They have played some wonderful cricket since they lost the first game in Chennai and are on the verge of winning the series and also securing a place in the WTC final. If India win, Virat Kohli will join Clive Lloyd with 36 wins as Test captain and with the way, things are going, the hosts are the favourites to make it 3 wins in a row.

Hello and a warm welcome to the fourth and final Test match between India and England. Three games done and one final one to go and this will decide who will go on to face New Zealand in the WTC final. England are out of contention but a win for them would mean that India are out as well and Australia will go through. But it won't be easy for the visitors as the hosts will be at their best to make it 3-1 and reach the final. India have a lot to play for as they can reach the top of the ICC rankings as well with a win. An exciting encounter awaits us.

England now trail by 160, they will need to score at least 350 if they are to think of winning this game. That though seems a long way away, their first aim will be to avoid an innings defeat. The wicket is still good enough to bat on so they would love to make use of that. They will come out for a bit before Lunch, can they come out of the nervy period unscathed? India, on the other hand, will love a wicket at least.

England did have their moments with the ball! They started off really well as they did not let India score freely and also picked up wickets at regular intervals. Anderson, Stokes and Leach, all three were good until the last session yesterday. One just feels they ran out of gas as runs started to flow in the last session of Day 2 and they did not look that threatening too. They failed to capitalize when they had a chance and that probably has put them well behind in the game.

Sundar walked out to bat when India were in a spot of bother, the game was in balance then as the hosts were 146 for 6. However, then came two stands which took the game away from England completely. First between Pant and Sundar with the former scoring a ton. He was dismissed yesterday but Patel and Sundar continued the good work. They too added another 100-run stand which took India's lead to over 150. Their innings came to a sour end as Axar was dismissed a little short of his first half ton and Sundar was left stranded at the non-striker's end 4 short of his first ton.

You have to feel so bad for Sundar who has his head down as he walks back quickly towards the dressing room. He does get a pat on his back from a few teammates as he makes his way back but he surely will be heartbroken as he was so close to his first Test ton. Nevertheless, he has done an exceptional job for his side.

OUT! TIMBER! Washington Sundar misses out on a well-deserved hundred as Siraj fails to survive. Good length ball around off, Siraj looks to defend but misses and the ball rattles the timber behind. Stokes ends up with a 4-fer. Sundar walks back a little disappointed but he has played a wonderful knock. INDIA ALL OUT FOR 365 WITH A LEAD OF 160.

One more delivery well wide outside off, it is left alone again.
Outside off, not played at.
Flatter and on off, Patel stays back and pushes it through covers for one.
A full toss, Sundar whips it down to long on for one.
This lands outside off and then spins away. Sundar plays inside the line and lets it go.
Another single as this is pushed down to long on.
Angled into the body, it is worked to mid-wicket for one.

Really good shot and very good fielding too! The 100-run stand is also up and this partnership is taking the game away from England completely. This is short and on middle, Sundar pulls it with one leg up in the air through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep makes good ground to his right, dives, stops it and then lets it go as he nears the ropes. They go upstairs to check and replays show that he has saved a run for his side.
Short and outside off, Sundar lets it go through to the keeper.
A bumper again, Patel hops and pulls it through mid-wicket for one. He played it nicely, all along the ground.
One more short one, it is ducked under.
On middle, it is blocked nicely.
Fuller and on off, Patel hits it hard down to long on and takes one.
Safe! Outside off, Patel lofts it over covers. Takes two. Lead now 150.

TWO BYES! This lands in the rough outside off. Patel goes hard at it. It pitches, spins and then takes off. Foakes has no chance, Stokes to fails to stop it as he dives to his right from first slip. Two taken as it goes down towards third man.
Outside off, Patel cuts but finds point.
A little too full, it is hit through covers for one.
Shorter one to end, this does not get up a lot. Patel sways away from it.
Another short one, Patel nudges it towards the leg side.
One more short one, this time Sundar pulls it through square leg for one.
Pulls it this time, nicely controlled and through square leg for one.
One more short one, Patel evades it.
A short one on middle, Patel ducks under it.
BEATEN! Quicker and outside off, Sundar looks to play it late but is beaten.
Shorter and on middle, Patel pulls it through mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, extravagant turn as it lands but it is from outside off. Left alone.
Fires it on middle, it is worked to mid on.
Nicely tossed up outside off, it turns away. Axar looks to go over covers but is beaten.
Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Patel this time gets on top of the bounce and defends it onto the ground.
5 short balls in a row now! Again ducked under.
One more short one, Axar picks it early and ducks under it.
Shorter this time again, Sundar pulls, not in total control but hits it well enough to get it over square leg. There is a fielder in the deep so just the one.
Edged but safe! An effort ball, gets it to rise, Axar looks to fend at it but the ball hits the splice and goes through the vacant gully region, down to third man for one.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.

DRINKS! India have done really well here at the start of Day 3! Axar Patel and Washington Sundar have bunted the bowling attack and have looked really good. Sundar is on his way to a century while Patel has played his part. England, on the other hand, need to break this partnership and get the remaining wickets as quickly as possible. They have a tough ask on their hands. Can they make a comeback?
Full on off, Patel defends it out.
Flatter ball outside off, Sundar punches it to deep cover for a single.
Low full toss on off, pushed to the off side.
Full on the pads, Patel works it wide of mid on for a single.
Full on off, Patel pushes it to mid off.
BEATEN! Terrific start from Root! Floated ball outside off, it spins away. Axar looks to defend but misses.
Joe Root is into the attack.
Good length ball on middle, Washington defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Sundar pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. Sundar has equalled his highest score in Tests.
Shortish outside off, Sundar lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball around middle, Sundar sways away from it. Well played by Sundar.
Fullish ball on off, Sundar pushes it to cover.
Very full ball on the pads, Sundar flicks it to fine leg and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full on off, Sundar uses his feet and then nudges it down to long on for a single.
Flighted ball on off, Sundar plays it out to the off side.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar defends it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Sundar defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! That was hit very hard! Brilliant batting from Sundar! Full on off, Sundar smacks it straight towards the bowler. It goes in between Leach's legs and goes for a boundary.
Floated on off, Sundar heaves it to mid-wicket.
Full on off, Patel plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball down the leg side, Axar looks to flick but seems to have missed it. Foakes appeals but he is the only one doing so. The umpire as well is not interested.
LEADING EDGE BUT SAFE! Full ball on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes past the cover fielder for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Sundar punches it back to the bowler.
Short ball around middle and leg, Sundar sways away from it.

Stokes starts with a very full ball on middle, Sundar looks to dig it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Stokes discusses with Root whether to take the review but decide against it.
Loopy ball on off, Patel looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the leg side.
Flighted ball outside off, Sundar pushes it to deep cover for a single.
On middle, nudged down to long on for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Axar nudges it to short leg.
SIX! Hammered! Flat six from the bat of Axar Patel! Flighted ball on off, Patel lifts it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Flighted ball on middle, Sundar uses his feet and then flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish ball on the pads, Axar works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball around middle, Patel ducks under it.
On middle and leg, pushed to mid on.
PLAY AND A MISS! Another excellent delivery from James Anderson! Full ball outside off, it moves away late. Full ball outside off, Patel looks to drive but misses.
Fullish ball on off, Patel prods forward and blocks it to cover.
Flatter ball on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but it brushes his pads and it goes to the leg side for a leg bye.
On the pads, Patel flicks it to square leg.
Slower through the air on middle, Axar flicks it to mid-wicket.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Flighted ball on off, Patel prods forward and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Loopy ball on off, Sundar works it down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Sundar prods forward and then defends it to cover.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball around middle, Patel ducks under it.
BEATEN! That's well bowled by Anderson! Fullish ball outside off, Patel looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on middle, Patel defends it back to the bowler.
Bouncer! It is bowled around middle, Patel ducks under it.
Short ball on middle, Sundar pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball on middle, Sundar looks to flick gets a top edge and it goes off the top half of the bat and onto the pitch.
FOUR! Brilliant from Axar Patel! Flatter ball outside off, Patel rocks on his back foot and then punches it  through the extra cover region for a boundary.
On off, defended out.
On the pads, Patel looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Flighted ball on middle, Axar flicks it to square leg.
FOUR! Played well! Calls for a catch but it is over the fielder! Flighted ball on middle, Patel smacks it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Flighted ball on off, Patel pushes it to mid off.
Jack Leach is into the attack.
Good length on the pads, Patel flicks it to the leg side and crosses over for a run.
Shortish on the pads, Sundar works it to deep square leg for a single.
There is a slight halt in play as Sundar seems to be in pain and the physio comes out to have a look at him.
On a length on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
A bouncer around off, Sundar looks to fend it away but misses as the ball goes to Foakes behind the stumps.
Full ball on middle, Patel drives it wide of mid on and takes a run.
Good length ball on off, Patel looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes towards the slip cordon.
Full on off, Sundar drives but the short cover fieder does well to dive and stop it.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar goes back in his crease and then defends it onto the pitch.
Loopy ball outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to it.
Flatter ball outside off, Sundar cuts it to point.
FOUR! This is even better by Sundar! Such superb timing! Bess struggles to find his rhythm. Low full toss on off, Sundar lunges forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
SIX! Excellent shot from Sundar! Brings up 300 in style! The lead moves to 100 as well. Flighted ball on middle, Sundar smacks it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Going down leg. Good length ball on the pads, Patel looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A mild appeal is made for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
Fullish ball way outside off, Patel lets it go to Foakes. Anderson has to make the batsmen play more often here.
Short ball around middle, Patel does well to duck under it.
On a length outside off, Patel lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball around off, Patel looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes to the gully region.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Patel.
Floated ball on off, Sundar strides forward and then plays it back to Bess.
Shortish and on off, Axar moves inside his crease and then punches it through the cover region for a single.
Slower through the air outside off, Axar lets it go to the keeper.
Loopy ball on off, Patel defends it to cover.
FOUR! Was in the air for a while but wide of the bowler! Flatter ball on off, Patel punches it uppishly but wide of the bowler and into the long off fence for a boundary.
An inside edge! Lovely start from Bess! Tossed up ball on off, Axar Patel looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Who will bowl from the other end? Dom Bess it is.
BEATEN! Excellent ball to end the over! Good length ball around off, it nips away a touch. Sundar looks to defend but it whizzes past the outside edge and goes to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Sundar makes another leave to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sundar once again has no problems in letting it go to the keeper.
Washington Sundar is in no hurry! Another on a length delivery outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Sundar watches it carefully and then lets it go to the keeper.
Anderson starts with a good length ball outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to this one.

We are all set to begin Day 3! The England players stride out to the middle, followed by Washington Sundar and Axar Patel. How long will England take to wrap up the Indian innings? James Anderson will start with the ball.

Will this be the last day in this Test match? It very well might be as England would need to bat out of their skins now to have a chance in this game but first they will need to pick up the remaining three wickets quickly. They have already given a lead of 89 runs and India are not done yet. The visitors' batting has been poor in this series and with a lead already being a good one for India, things look bleak for England in this series and the chances for India going to the WTC final has increased massively.

Day 3 which is also called the moving day is upon us with India ahead in the game. They lead by 89 runs and are looking set for a good lead over the visitors. India were not ahead all the time, in fact, England had won the first 2 sessions on Day 2 but Pant's majestic century along with Sundar's innings helped the hosts gain the advantage towards the end of Day 2. The hosts would now look to press home the advantage and put England out of the contest. England, on the other hand, would be disappointed that they let go of the advantage that they had got and now are on the back foot. They would hope to wrap up the innings as quickly as possible and then bat extremely well to get back in the game. An exciting day coming up.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

So, India are well and truly in pole position of this Test match, sealing their place in the WTC final and also winning the trophy. England will have to take good rest overnight, ensure they come fresh and motivated on Day 3. They will first need to find a way to wrap up this innings and then ensure the batters can finally deliver. Make sure you join us on Saturday, 6th March for Day 3 of this Test. The action begins at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Till then goodbye and take care!

The star of the day, Rishabh Pant is caught down for a chat! Pant tells that the only thing running on his mind was building a stand with Rohit. Says after assessing the pitch, he played his shots. Tells that he understood that he will have to respect the good ball. Feels he knew the bad balls will come and that's when he will score his runs. Tells that he likes to play according to the situation. Says that the plan was to get to England's score and then get a big lead. On the reverse sweep against Anderson, Pant says that it was a pre-meditated shot. Tells that he gets the license to go for the big shots but says that he assess the situation and goes for the shots. Ends by saying that his aim is to play and make the team win and if the crowd gets entertained because of him, he is happy doing that as well.

On a scorching hot day, credit must be given to Ben Stokes and Jimmy Anderson. The pair kept running and ran out of steam but kept going. England's gamble to play a bowler short was looking like it was paying off but not to be. Bess struggled for rhythm and his lack of confidence was evident.  That saw the burden increase on the pacers and Root had to shoulder a lot of responsibility. The two pacers did well. Veteran Anderson and Stokes both picked up two today while Leach too got a brace.

But then the tide changed, the momentum shifted, and the game turned on its head. Rishabh Pant and Washington Sundar joined hands, and both the young left-handers took on the England bowlers. While Sundar kept tiring the bowlers by playing a classic Test match knock. Pant, from the other end, was taking on the attack. The Delhi lad who has this knack of deciding a Test with his batting did the same. Pant scored a supreme century and Washington showed his mettle as well. The pair added 113,  a stand that saw India take the lead not just on the scorecard but also in the larger context of the game. Pant's majestic innings came to an end but Washington carried his merry way. He reached his fifty and with Axar they have also extended their team's lead and tired the tourists out on a hot, hot day.

England started the day just how the doctor ordered. They kept things tight initially and managed to pick wickets at regular intervals. At 80/4 it looked like India was in trouble. That trouble seemed to have deepened when the well-set batter, Rohit Sharma departed for 49. Ashwin and Pant tried to steady the ship but the off-spinner did not last long. At 146/6, still trailing by 59 on a pitch where batting was not at all easy. It was England who were happy and smiling.

What a fantastic day of Test cricket. England won the first two sessions but a young southpaw from Delhi ensured that India don't just win the final session but win it in such a way that the day belonged to the hosts. The day belonged to Rishabh Pant and all headlines will have his name and rightfully so but Washington Sundar has played a superb inning himself and has finished the day unbeaten on 60!
And he does that nicely. Floated full and around off, Axar comes on the front foot and blocks it. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Floated full and down the leg side. Axar looks to flick but misses. Foakes does superbly well to collect to his right. Just one ball left for Axar to negotiate.
Appeal again but turned down. England are not going for the DRS. This one is tossed up wide outside off, Axar brings out his pad and pushes it away. An appeal for LBW but turned down.
Flat and around middle and leg, it keeps low. Axar does well to get his bat down in time to block.
Loopy ball around off, kept out.
Beaten! Flat and just outside off, Patel looks to force it on the off side but misses.
DRS TIME! Sundar has been given out LBW. He goes for the review quickly. Looks like there is some bat. Yes, there is. Ultra Edge confirms.

NOT OUT! Big spike off the bat. Sundar is safe and he used the DRS nicely. Bess bowls a lovely ball again. Lands it around middle and in spins in sharply. Sundar looks to keep it out but misses to get hit on the pad. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Sundar is quick to signal the 'T'. Time for the replays. Well, well, Bess has to wait for his first wicket. Ultra Edge shows big spike. Excellent use of the review.
Flat and around middle, Sundar blocks.
Floated full and around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.

NOT OUT! Sundar is safe! He never want out. That was lovley ball from Bess though. He lands it around off and it spins away to beat the forward prod of Sundar. Foakes collects and takes the bails off. The square leg refers it upstairs.
On off, blocked.

In the air... safe! Sundar would've had his heart in his mouth. Good from Bess again. Teases the batsman with a tossed up ball outside off, Sundar looks to go big over the off side but the ball spins away and Sundar ends up slicing it high in the air. However, it keeps going away from Anderson who tries to get under it form mid off. He cannot get there. Two taken.
Flat and around off, Patel is solid in defense.
Shortish and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one more easy single.
Short and spinning in from outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for one.
Floated on off, spins in. Axar looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to leg gully.
Flat and around off, pushed on the off side for nothing.
On middle, kept out.
Floated around off, kept out by Sundar. A much-better over from Bess. A maiden from him, his first of the innings.
On off, Sundar blocks.
Full and around off, poked off the front foot towards the cover region.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Floated around off, Sundar comes on the front foot and blocks.
Loopy fuller ball outside off, driven to the cover region.
FOUR! Axar goes for the shot now! Tossed up ball on middle, Axar hits it through the line and does so over square leg. A couple of bounces and into the fence. 9 off this over.
FOUR BYES! Foakes cannot collect this one. This one lands on middle and spins in sharply. Patel cannot flick. Foakes cannot collect it down the leg side. Goes to the fine leg fence for four byes.
Floated full and around off, played back to the bowler.
On off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
WIDE! Slipped down the leg side. Axar looks to flick but misses.
Flat and around off, turns in. Sundar clips it through mid-wicket for one.
Bess is clearly down on confidence. Root was seen having a word with his bowler at the end of the over. Good from the skipper to back his bowler.
Tossed up and outside off, Sundar gives him a charge and looks to flick it on the leg side. Ends up getting a leading edge that goes to deep cover for one.
Full ball outside off, driven towards the cover fielder who makes a diving stop.
On off, solidly kept out.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
FOUR! Another gift from Bess. This hasn't been his day to be honest but then you cannot bowl dollies like this at this level. Juicy full toss, Sundar strokes it over Bess and finds the fence.
Floated around off, Sundar blocks off the front foot.
Bess is back too! He has struggled for rhythm and that has hurt his side. Can Bess find his groove?
Looped up and outside off, Patel is on the front foot to block.
Flat and around off, Axar blocks nicely.
Loopy ball outside off, Axar looks to drive but the ball spins in and takes the inner half. Goes to mid-wicket.
Turning in from middle, Axar looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Leach arrives and beats the bat straightaway. Tosses it up and just outside off, Axar looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
Leach is back! Jack Leach is back on! 2/59 from his 19 overs.
Short and wide outside off, cut to deep point for one.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Banged short but down the leg side. Patel looks to pull but misses.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep point for a single.

FIFTY FOR SUNDAR! Wonderful innings from the young man. His third in the format. A fuller ball outside off, Sundar steers it past the man at gully. It is racing to the fence. However. Bess runs to his right and makes a fine stop with a dive. Saves two but Sundar gets to his half-century.
FOUR! Sundar moves to 48. A stunning stroke to get there. Fuller ball outside off, Sundar slams it through backward point and finds the fence.
Ben Stokes is back into the attack.
Looped up and outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Floated on middle, kept out.
On off, Patel comes on the front foot to push it back to Root.
Fired on middle, tucked towards the man at short leg.
FOUR! Hammered! Too short from Root and Axar nails the pull through mid-wicket. A boundary for him.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Just outside off on a length, poked on the off side for nothing. 5 runs and a wicket from the over.

FOUR! Shot of the day? Surely one of the contenders. A length ball just outside off, Sundar punches it on the up and hits it wide of the man at mid off. This time the fielder cannot stop to his right.
Full and wide outside off, driven wide of the man at mid off who makes a sliding half stop to his right. A single taken.
Too full and around middle, kept out.
In the channel outside off, Axar lets it be.
Local boy Axar Patel walks out to bat now. He is capable with the willow in hand but so far in his minute Test career, he has not done much with the bat. Can he deliver with the bat as well now?

OUT! TAKEN! Pant falls now! But not before playing a majestic Test ton. Take a bow, champion. He is mighty disappointed as he heads back to the pavilion. The crowd is standing to appreciate the show-stopper. You live by the sword, you die by it. Pant loves this quote and he often lives up to it. A shortish ball outside off, Pant looks to drag the pull on the leg side. He though ends up hitting it off the toe end. The ball goes straight to the English skipper who makes no mistake. End of a magnificent knock from Pant. He is disappointed big time as he walks back. Hits his pad with the willow but what a knock. India lead by 54.
On middle again. Sundar blocks off the front foot.
Floated on middle, played back to the bowler.
On middle, kept out.
Fuller and outside off, driven through the covers for one.
Flatter and just outside off, punched towards the cover region.

SIX! CENTURY FOR PANT! Century with a biggie! Take a bow, young man. What an unbelievable knock this has been from him. He has just grown in stature ever since his return to the Indian Test side. This man is just too good. A fine, fine knock, one that has been challenging. He walked in when the team was in big, big trouble but he has bailed them out and now have taken them to a strong, strong position. The crowd has gone mad in the stadium. And what a shot to get to the milestone. Root comes in and tosses the ball around middle, Pant gets down and mows the sweep over deep backward square leg for a biggie. Takes the helmet off and raises the bat. Sundar gives him a hug. This is Pant's 3rd Test ton, first in India.
Length ball around off, worked towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Back of a length and on middle, Sundar tucks it towards deep mid-wicket and scampers back for two more.
Short ball, Pant swivels and pulls it to fine leg for a single. 250 up for the hosts.
Sundar has a word with Pant. These two have played together for India in U-19 cricket. And they have turned things on here. India lead by 44 at the moment.
Gives the bowler a charge this time but fails to connect and gets hit high on the pad.
Shortish and around off, Pant taps it on the off side and calls for a single but Sundar is not keen. And that makes Pant unhappy.

FOUR! WOW! Pant! What a player! A reverse sweep against a pacer. Against a pacer of the quality of Anderson. Genius. Fullish ball around off, Pant nails the the reverse sweep and hits it over the slip cordon for a boundary. 100-run stand is up between the two as well.
Wide outside off on a length. This time Sundar makes a leave. 13 off the over. 22 off the first 2 overs off the second new ball.
FOUR! Third boundary in the over. Poor from Stokes. Short and wide outside off, Sundar slashes it over gully and finds the fence again.
Gets behind the line of the delivery this time to solidly block it.
FOUR! Classy from Sundar now. These two are turning things on here. A short ball from Stokes and it is wide as well. Sundar crunches the cut through point and bags another boundary.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed wide of mid off for one.

FOUR! WOW! This is just too good from Pant at the moment. A fuller ball outside off, Pant goes for the drive but fails to connect it well. But he goes throught he shot. It takes the inside edge and goes wide of the man at mid on. And guess what? It goes to the fence.
Good length ball around off, Washington taps it to point. 9 off the first over from the second new ball. Not the start England would have wanted. The lead now stands at 27!
Fuller on off, Pant pushes it to mid on for one.

What a jaffa! Superb comeback from Anderson. He hist the deck hard and makes the ball shape just a bit away from the southpaw. Pant looks to defend but that extra zip off the surface and little movement sees him miss it.
Fuller around off, Pant drives it straight to the cover fielder.
FOUR! SLAPPED! Length ball outside off, Pant swots it through covers for a boundary. This is top-class batting from Pant!
FOUR! Welcome to the attack, new ball and Anderson! Pant comes down the track and smacks it over mid off for a boundary.

The second new ball is available now. Root might take it immediately as this old ball has not done much in this session so far. James Anderson is brought into the attack as the new ball has been taken.
FOUR! Supreme from Washington! Stokes obverpitches it on middle. Sundar drives it through mid on. Stokes flies but to no avail. The ball goes to the fence.
Short ball outside off, Sundar sways away from it.
Another single. This time Pant runs it down to third man and gets a single to move to 75.
Stokes hits the deck hard outside off, Sundar punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Length delivery on off, Sundar defends it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Washington defends it.

DRINKS! India's best hour of play with the bat in this Test and thanks to their X-factor, Rishabh Pant and Washington Sundar they have taken the lead in this innings and in this game.  England have looked jaded in this session so far and are now looking out of ideas. They are still not out of this game but they need some inspiration to get back in this game.

NOT OUT! Missing the stumps. Pant is safe and he will continue his battle. It was the slider from Root. Pant stayed back in and tried to flick but missed to get hit on the back leg. A loud appeal but turned down by the umpire. The skipper has a word with his keeper and Stokes and they go for the review. Looked really close. Let's see what the replays have got to show. Ultra Edge first, to confirm if there was any bat. Clear gap between bat and pad. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Missing. Pant survives. England lose their review.
Review time! England have taken a review against Rishabh Pant for LBW. Let's see if the replays can help England break this stand.
Short and wide outside off, cut towards backward point.
FOUR! This time off the meat of the willow. What a blow from Pant. Tossed up and on middle, he gets down and nails the sweep. All along the ground and into the fence at deep square leg.

EDGY FOUR! More frustration for England and Stokes. Tossed up and outside off, Pant gors for the slog sweep. He ends up getting it off the toe end. The ball goes over the keeper. Stokes from the first slip gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Floated outside off, spinning away. Pant lets it be. Looks like anything in his zone will wallop over the fence.
Full and outside off, Pant comes down the track and hits it towards the short cover fielder.
In the channel outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
A beamer now! Stokes asks for an apology from the batter straightaway. Clearly he is frustrated now. A high full toss. Sundar does well to fend it away.
Angled in from middle, Stokes tucks it to deep mid-wicket and takes one.
Full and wide outside off, driven wide of mid off for two. India are into the lead now.
The crowd is chanting the name of Pant now. He is now the leading run-scorer of this series. Now, Stokes loses the ball while in the delivery stride. Kicks the ball in anger.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! That is off the middle of the bat. The scores are level now. Stokes runs in and bangs it short. Pant nails the pull and hits it along the ground. It goes to the deep square leg fence.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard. A length ball outside off, Pant goes for the cut but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the second slip fielder and into the third man fence. 200 up for India.

Big turn! Tossed up and outside off, lands and spins away sharply as Sundar looks to go big, inside out. Makes no connection. The ball hits the gloves of Foakes and lobs up to the left side of Stokes who does well to catch. There was no bat though.
Fired on middle and leg, kept out by Washington.
Floated around off, Sundar is solid in defense.
Flat and around middle, kept out off the back foot.
Loopy ball outside off, driven towards the cover region.
Floated on middle, Sundar looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and just around off, Pant wanted to go for the pull but at the last moment decided against it and punched it to mid off.
Fullish ball around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for an easy single.
Sharp bouncer! Sundar sways away from the firing line.
In the channel, just outside off. Watchful leave from Sundar.
Bouncer on middle and leg. Sundar sits under it.
Good length and just outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Change in bowling. Ben Stokes is being reintroduced into the attack.
Another one fired outside off. Pant leaves it alone.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Shortish and just outside off, punched through the covers for one. 50-run stand is up between the two. Fine, fine association for India between the two.
Flat and around off, Sundar pushes it off his back foot on the off side.
On off, kept out.
Full and on middle, played back to the bowler.
FOUR! SHOT! WHIPPED BY PANT! Loopy fuller ball on middle, Pant flicks it over square leg. One bounce and into the fence. India trail by just 10 now. The stand moves to 49 between the two.
Another easy run! Flat and on middle, it is worked through backward square leg for a single.
Full ball on middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, flicked to mid-wicket for one.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Sundar takes a stride forward to block.
Loopy ball around off, Pant is solid in defense of the front foot.
Short and wide outside off, crunched straight to the man at backward point.
Close leave, a good one at that. That wasn't too far away from the off pole. Darted just outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket by Pant.
Shortsih ball on middle, worked towards fine leg for one.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for an easy single.
On the pads, tucked towards the leg side.

FIFTY FOR PANT! His 7th in Tests and 3rd in this series. This has been a very good knock from the young keeper. He is enjoying a rich vein of form and he has done the job fantastically. His innings might be the difference between winning and losing. On a pitch where most batsmen are struggling, he has looked very comfortable. Only Indian batter in this innings to get to a fifty. On the pads, Pant comes down and whips it to the on side for a single.
Quicker on off, Pant defends it with a straight bat.
Short on the pads, Pant tickles it to short fine leg.
On the pads, Pant flicks it but to short leg.

Appeal for LBW but turned down and Root does not take the review. Darted quicker around off, Sundar looks to defend but seems to have missed it and the ball hits the pad. There is an appeal but the umpire is no interested.
Again short on the pads. Sundar whips it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
Floated on off, Sundar defends it off the front foot.
Arm ball outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
Short on off, Sundar whips it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. Takes the partnership to 37 and reduces the trail to 22.
Flighted on off, Sundar pushes it to mid off.
Dot to finish teh over. Pant is stranded on 49. Floated around off, Pant plays it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off and middle, Washington milks it to long on and gives the strike to Pant.
NO BALL! Short on middle, Pant pulls it to deep square leg and gets a single. Moves to 49 with that. Leach has also overstepped here.
Leach is bowling too short here. This is knocked to long on for a single.
Impact outside! Floated outside off, Sundar leans forward to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad. Foakes is the only one going up in an appeal.
Tossed up on middle, Sundar defends it.
Floated on off, Washington blocks it.
Flighted on off, Washington drives it to mid off and keeps the strike with a good single.
Tossed up on off, Sundar defends it.
Tossed up on the stumps, Washington blocks it.
Short around off, Washington punches it to the right of Leach at cover.
Short around off, Pant taps it to the left of cover-point and gets a single.
Flatter on off, Pant defends it to point.
Flighted on off, Pant pushes it to point and takes the first one quickly. He wants the second but Sundar is in no mood to take the chance against the arm of Stokes.
On middle and short, Pant blocks.
Short around middle, Pant looks to defend off his back foot but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
Down the leg side, Pant misses his flick.
Shortish and on the pads, worked towards fine leg for a run.
Shortish ball around off to begin from Leach. Clipped through mid-wicket for one by Pant.
Jack Leach is on now.
On middle, Sundar defends it solidly.
Flat again. This is around off, Sundar pokes it back to the bowler.
Flat and outside off, poked towards backward point for nothing.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Sundar looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
On middle, clipped towards square leg for one.

FOUR! Up and over! Fine shot from Sundar. Tossed up and outside off, he drives it uppishly over the man at covers who leaps to catch but Sundar times it nicely. The ball goes to the fence in the deep. Good way to end the over.
Loopy and around off, pushed to mid off.
The physio is out now to have a look at Pant's shoulder. Might need some magic spray for relief as that has hurt him.

Confusion but safe in the end. Had he hit, could have been a big, big wicket for England. A full ball around off, Sundar drives it towards mid off. Pant wants a single but is sent back. Lawrence has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses as Pant dives to make his ground. The throw hits Pant near the shoulder.
Floated outside off, spins a touch away further. Left alone by Sundar.
Slower fuller ball around off, Sundar defends.
Full ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Flat and around off, kept out. Tight over from Root.

Big turn! This one lands just outside off and spins away sharply. Sundar comes on the front foot to block but the ball spins away to beat the outside edge. Foakes collects and takes the bails off in a flash but Sundar never went outside the crease.
Floated full and around off, kept out.
Flat and around off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Shortish ball on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one. Pant wanted the second but they opted against it.
Floated around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.
Once again he comes down the track and hits it down to long off for a single.
Floated around off, Pant comes down the track and blocks it. Didn't get to the pitch there and did well to keep it out.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Poor bowling from Bess. Short and wide outside off. Pant rocks back and cranks it through the covers. It races away to the fence in the deep. He moves into the 40s.
Dropped short this time. Sundar thumps it to deep cover for one.
FOUR! And he begins with a gift for Sundar. Washington won't mind it. A full toss on the pads, Sundar flicks it through mid-wicket and finds the fence.
Who will partner Joe Root from the other end? Dom Bess it is.
Tossed up and outside off, Sundar drives it through the covers for one. The lead now stands at 50.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
Flat and around off, Sundar looks to flick but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad.
Floated on middle, Sundar defends it on the leg side. A bit of an appeal from Root and from the keeper too. Not out says the umpire. No review. Looked to be inside edge.
Full and around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.
Loopy ball outside off, driven through the covers for a single by Pant.
It is time for the final session. The English players make their way to the middle. Rishabh Pant will resume his innings along with Washington Sundar. Joe Root will begin with the ball. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Another decent bowling performance from England. Once again it is Stokes who put a spirited effort and bowled a long spell and prized out the massive wicket of Rohit Sharma. Leach got rid of Ashwin and have kept the team in this game. A couple of quick wickets and they still have the chance of taking a decent lead. Join us for the final session to find out how things pan out.

The session started well for the Indians as Rohit along with Pant added runs without much trouble. However, England didn't give easy runs, as they did in the first session. Rohit fell for 49 but Pant continued. Ashwin failed to last long and departed for 13. Pant has continued and has done well to keep the Indians in the game. He has Sundar for the company and the duo will return with the aim of taking the team close to the English total and then take the lead.

A very good session of play. Both the teams would feel that they have done a fine job. England managed the big wicket of Rohit after India were starting to take the game away. And for India, as far as Pant is there, they are always in the game. They are still 52 behind but Pant can wipe these runs off in no time.
Flighted ball outside off, asking Washington to drive but the southpaw is happy to leave it alone and go to Tea unscathed. TEA ON DAY 2!
Floted outside off and spinning away. Washington leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, Washington keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Washington defends it.
Floated on middle, Pant knocks it to long on for one.
DRS TIME! Drama before the Tea break. It is against Pant for the LBW. No bat involved. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Pant survives a big scare.

NOT OUT! Pant survives! The ball is hitting the stumps but not enough to reverse the on-field call. Shortish delivery pitching on middle. It pitches and does not spin. It comes quicker. Pant looks to flick it off his back foot. He misses and gets hit on the back foot. There is a huge cry for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Root, Bess, and Foakes have a chat and the skipper takes it upstairs. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows two reds but one yellow. The ball is hitting the stumps on umpire's call. Good enough to save the review but not enough to overturn the decision.
Short on off, Washington defends it. Looks like we will have one more over before Tea.
Tossed up on off, Washington blocks it.
Flighted on off, Sundar lunges forward and blocks it.
Around off, Pant punches it to cover and gets one.
On the pads, Pant whips it behind square leg and gets a couple to bring up the 150 for India. They trail by 54.
Floated on off, Root gets a little turn. Pant does well to defend it off his back foot.
Short outside off, Pant knocks it to long on and keeps the strike.
Short and little bit of bounce to go with the turn. Pant blocks it.
Short around off, Sundar cuts it through point and gets off the mark with a single.
Floated on off, Pant pushes it to the off side for a run.
Floated around off, Pant looks to play the reverse sweep but gloves it to point.
Straighter one outside off. Pant leaves it alone.
Flighted on leg, Sundar defends it to see off the over. Wicket maiden for Leach.
Floated on off, Sundar is keen to get off the mark. He comes down the track and hits it back to Leach.
Tossed up on pff, this time Sundar drives to the right of the bowler. Leach dives again and keeps Sundar waiting on a duck.
Flighted around off, Sundar lunges forward and plays it to the left of Leach. He dives and denies Sundar the single.
Flatter on off, Sundar taps it to point.
Who is in next? It is Washington Sundar.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jack Leach gets the wicket but where has this come from? Ashwin and Pant both were looking good out in the middle and this one has somewhat come against the run of play. Jack Leach has bowled well and worked hard and has got his reward. Floated delivery on the pads, the ball stops on the surface before coming to Ashwin. He looks to flick it to the leg side and give the strike to Pant but because the ball stops on the surface, Ashwin's flick is uppish and straight to Pope at short mid-wicket. He makes no mistake and India 6 down and they still trail by 59. Second wicket of the session. Can England get another one before the end of this session?
Length ball on off, Pant defends it to the off side and looks to steal a quick single. Ashwin though is quick to turn it down. No need to take any risky runs here.
On off, kept out.

NOT OUT! The dive has saved Rishabh Pant! Good cricket all-around. Another good indipper from Stokes. It is on middle and off, Ashwin manages to get bat on ball. The ball goes to the on side. Ashwin calls for the run straightaway. Pant is quick to respond. Bairstow gets to the ball quickly and scores a direct hit. Pant puts in a dive and that sees him get back in time.
Has the dive saved him?
BS continues to hit the deck hard on middle. Ashwin defends it.
Back of a length delivery around off, Ashwin taps it to point.
Short on middle, Ashwin tucks it to the on side.

DROPPED! Harsh but technically a drop. Would have been a spectacular catch. Short on the pads, Pant flicks it uppishly but also very hard. Pope at short leg, gets his hands to it but cannot hold onto it. That was hit very hard so was never going to be easy at all.
FOUR! Nicely punched and the trail now is 60! Short and spinning in, Pant goes on his back foot and punches it against the spin through covers for a boundary.
Good running! Leach bowls this slower and gives this air on off. Ashwin nudges it towards point and gets a single.
Floated on middle, Ashwin defends it on the front foot.
Short around off, Pant whips it with the spin through mid-wicket. Pant needed two but Aswin says no. Pant in the stump mic, can be heard, saying good call.
Spinning in a bit. Pant goes on his back foot and defends it.
Bouncer! Ashwin ducks under it.
Stokes hits the deck hard outside off. Ashwin looks to defend but then pulls his bat back inside the line.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it right of the middle but it is straight to square leg.
Back of a length ball around off, Pant runs it down to third man for a single.
Slower ball from Stokes but he misses his line and bowls it down the leg side.
Full outside off, Pant drives it straight to Bairstow at short cover.
Short and turning away, Ashwin taps it to point.
Tossed up around off, Ashwin keeps it out.
On the pads, Pant flicks it to the on side and gets to the other end.

EDGED BUT SAFE! This one spins off the rough. Pant looks to defend off his back foot but gets a little inside edge. It lobs off his pad to the left of Foakes. He is wrong-footed but still dives. Unfortunately for the visitors to no avail.
Floated around off, Pant sweeps it to short fine leg.

Overthrows! Leach vs Pant and the Indian keeper has already used his feet. Pant comes down the track and looks to push it to mid on. He misses and gets hit on the pad. They take a leg bye. There is an unnecessary shy at the stumps which allows them to take an extra run.
Wide outside off, Ashwin watches it go behind.
On a length and outside off, kept out.
Good length and around off, pushed towards the cover region.

EDGY FOUR! Ashwin would've had his heart in his mouth there. Stokes runs in and serves a length ball outside off, Ashwin goes for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the slip cordon and the ball races away to the fence.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Ultra Edge. Ashwin survives. That was a lovely ball from Stokes. A sharp bouncer it was from Stokes once again. Ashwin looks to run it down to the third man region for a single. However, he misses and the ball goes behind. Foakes collects and England celebrate. Ashwin quickly calls for the DRS. Here comes the replays. Looks really close as the ball goes past the bat. Ultra Edge will clear things. Here it comes. Nothing on it. The sound was the ball hitting the shoulder. Ashwin survives. Good use of the DRS from Ashwin.

Ashwin has reviewed it straightaway! He has been adjudged caught behind but he has not wasted a moment to signal the 'T'. This indicates that there is no bat involved. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Back of a length ball around off, pulled to deep square leg for one.
This time Leach gives the ball a lot of air. Ashwin comes on the front foot to block. A maiden from Leach.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin looks to punch it on the off side but misses.
Flat and just around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
On middle, worked towards the leg side for nothing.
Flat and just outside off, kept out.
Floated around off, Ashwin blocks.
Jack Leach is back into the attack. It will be interesting to see how Pant goes against the left-arm spinner but first, he will start with Ashwin.
Good bumper to end the over! This rises off the deck from good length. Ashwin wanted to sit under it but was late. The ball hits the bat and drops on the leg side. They cross for a run.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Gift! This time from Stokes. Full toss and wide outside off, Ashwin said thank you and creams it through the covers.
Slips this one down the leg side. Ashwin misses out on the flick.
Shortish and around middle, Ashwin looks to defend but ends up getting a soft leading edge. The ball drops just in front of him.
Fuller ball on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on who runs to his left and dives to stop. Single taken.
Darted on middle and leg, spinning in. Ashwin fends it to the man at short fine leg. He wanted a single but a loud no from Pant.
Loopy ball around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Soft hands from Ashwin. A shortish ball around off, Ashwin stays back and pokes it past the man at slip. Two taken.
Tossed up and outside off, poked through backward point for one.
Flat and on middle, kept out.
Ravichandran Ashwin has joined Pant out in the middle! He scored a century in the second Test in a pitch that was not an easy one to bat on. Can Ashwin once again deliver with the bat?

DRINKS! Just when it looked like India were getting back on top, Stokes has come in and got the big wicket of Rohit Sharma to keep things in balance. India still have Sundar and Ashwin along with Axar. All three are capable with the willow in hand. Pant is out in the middle as well and one will feel he will be crucial in this game now. His attacking approach can turn the tide of this game in the blink of an eye. It is not an easy pitch to bat on and Pant will need to take calculated risks from here on. England will hope to continue their good work with the ball and bowl India under 205 and if not that then at least not give them a telling lead. Can the visitors continue their impressive showing with the ball?

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Rohit will have to take the long walk back to the pavilion on 49. Massive, massive wicket. It is that man Stokes again. He can do no wrong with the ball. Lovely delivery from Stokes. He gets this ball to jag back in sharply after pitching outside off. Rohit is late in getting his bat down. He gets hit on the back leg. A massive appeal follows and the finger goes up. Stokes roars. He is fired up and why wouldn't he be. This is such a huge wicket. Rohit after having a discussion with his partner goes for the review. Replays roll in. Ultra Edge detects nothing. Ball Tracker time now. Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. The review remains but Rohit has to go. A fine effort but India needed him to go big.

Rohit Sharma has been adjudged LBW on 49! He has had a long chat with Pant and has decided to take it upstairs. He does not look too confident and by his body language, it looks like he has just taken a chance here.
Angles the length ball from middle, Rohit looks to work it on the leg side but he squares up a touch and the ball goes towards the cover fielder.
Fullish and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Shortish ball around middle, tucked on the leg side of the wicket.
Outside off on a length, pushed towards backward point for nothing.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards the gully region where the fielder makes a fine stop.
Change from both ends. Anderson has been given a well-deserved break. He is replaced by Ben Stokes.
Loopy and around middle, Pant keeps it out.

SIX! BANG GOES PANT NOW! He doesn't want Root to settle. Tossed up and around off and middle, Pant puts the dancing shoes on and bangs it over mid off for a biggie. He moves to 20 and the stand between the two moves to 41.
On off, played to mid off.

WOW! Stunning stroke! Stunning fielding. Superb cricket overall. Looped ball on middle and leg, Pant brings out the reverse sweep. Nails it wide of the man at deep covers. Crawley there makes a good ground to his right and makes a fine save. Two saved.
Full and on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for one. Rohit moves to 49.
Floated around off to begin, kept out off the front foot.
Change in bowling. First one of the session.  It sees Bess being replaced by the skipper, Joe Root.
Full again and outside off again. Pant drives but finds the cover fielder.
Fuller and on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
Another fullish ball and it is outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Driven nicely! Second boundary for Pant. A bit too wide and fuller too. Rishabh leans into the drive and hits it through the covers to bag a boundary.
Outside off on a good length. Poked towards backward point for nothing.
Around off on a good length. Pant is solid in defense.
Anderson continues.
On middle, Rohit defends calmly.
Quick single! Floated full and on the pads, Pant comes down the track and hits it hard mid on. Calls for a quick single as it goes wide of Bess who dives to his left but cannot stop.
Floated around middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for an easy run.
Flat and around middle, worked towards the on side.
Uppish but wide! Floated around middle, Rohit looks to defend. The ball spins in a touch. It hits the upper part of the bat and lobs wide of the man at short leg.
Full toss outside off, Pant comes down the track and hits it down to long off for an easy run.
Will Bess continue? He has been leaking runs and letting off the pressure on India. Root is still showing his faith in his off-spinner and continues with him.
Good length and outside off, punched to the off side for nothing.
Fullish and around middle, kept out.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Shortish and on middle, worked on the leg side.
Anderson once again loses his run-up.

FOUR! BOOM! Too short and too wide. Rohit has been in the middle for a long time now. He crunches it between gpoint and the cover fielder. One of the fielders gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. India trail by exactly 100 runs.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed to mid off.
Pant gives it a charge and looks to go big over the off side. Fails to time it well. 'Catch it' is the cry from the keeper but it lands well short of mid off.
Loopy ball just outside off, played back to Pant.
Shortish and turning away. Pant waits and then taps it towards point.
Floated on middle, eased a run through mid off.
Slips this one down the leg side. Left alone.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Rohit moves into the 40s. Bess tosses it up and bowls it wide outside off. Rohit leans the drive through extra cover and it races away to the fence.
Serves a fullish ball around off, Pant defends.
Anderson runs in but loses his balance in the delivery stride.
Outside off, Pant makes a leave.
Length ball around off, Pant defends it out.
Fullish and around off, kept out.
Around off on a length, Pant looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg.
Back of a length ball around off, Pant pokes it towards backward point. Wants a single but Rohit loudly says, 'Are nahi', meaning, no, no.
Short and very close to the off pole. Pant punches it to sweeper cover and keeps the strike. A much better over from Bess.
Loopy ball around off. Pant comes down the track and takes it as a full toss. Pant pushes it to the bowler.
Pant comes down the track and takes this fuller. He pushes it to the right of Bess. He gets to the ball and threatens to throw it at the keeper's end but does not.
Bess gives this one a lot of air and bowls it slow. Pant gets on his front foot and defends it.
Darted fuller on off and middle, Pant pushes it back to Bess.
Short around the body, Rohit pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Pant leaves it alone. An edgy boundary came of the over. Anderson's figure reads 14-10-11-2! Just unbelievable!
On off, Pant keeps it out.
Anderson pulls his length back outside off. Pant looks to defend but misses.

EDGED AND FOUR! Anderson goes fuller on off, Pant looks to defend but does so with soft hands. The ball shapes away from the southpaw. It catches the outside edge and goes between gully and first slip to the third man fence.
Good length ball outside off, Pant has a poke but misses.
Good length and outside off, Pant lets it be.
Flat and on middle, tucked to square leg for nothing.
On off, kept out.
Floated around off, played back to the bowler.
FOUR! Freebie and Rohit is not going to miss out. Full toss outside off, Rohit creams it through the covers and bags another boundary.
Shortish and outside off, spins in. Pushed to mid on for nothing.
Floated on middle, Pant comes down the track and strokes it down to long on to open his account.
Around off on a length, Rohit is solid in defense. A maiden.
Good length and around off, Rohit comes on the front foot to defend. The ball takes the inside edge and goes to mid-wicket.
Driven firmly but straight to mid off. Anderson serves a full ball around off, Rohit finds mid off.
Back of a length and on middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Around off on a length, pushed to mid on.
Floated around off, Pant blocks.
Floated on middle, eased down to long on for an easy single.
FOUR BYES! This one turns big after lading on middle. It was short as well. Rohit looks to pull but it spins in sharply. Rohit misses, the keeper misses and it goes to the fine leg fence.
On middle, flicked wide of the man at mid-wicket. They do not go for the single.
Floated around off, Rohit is on the front foot to block.
Floated on middle, Rohit allows the ball to hit him high on the pad.
Who will bowl the first proper over of the session? Will it be the off spin of Bess or the left-arm spin of Leach? It is going to be Dom Bess!
Anderson bowls it wide outside off and on a good length. Left alone.
We are back again! The English players are out in the middle. Rohit Sharma walks out along with a new partner in Rishabh Pant. Anderson has one ball left of his over. Pant to face. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

So, three big wickets in the session for England. However, India still have Rohit in the middle. They are still 125 behind. Rohit has done all the hard work so far and now will look to convert this into a big score. He though will need support from the other end. England would like to see him sitting in the pavilion as quickly as possible. Important second session coming up shortly.

England were superb with the ball. Anderson and Stokes started nicely. Anderson was taken off and Leach arrived. He bowled tightly and struck to send Pujara in the hut. Stokes was terrific in his spell. He troubled Pujara and then sent the Indian skipper packing for a duck. Rohit and Rahane association took the attack to them but Anderson got the big wicket of Rahane at the stroke of Lunch. This has been a sensational session for England and they would be mighty pleased with their effort this morning.

The Indians started a bit too sedately and that did not go in their favor. Rohit and Pujara were happy to keep blocking. Not sure if that was the right approach as runs were almost dried up. You never see something like that with Rohit in the middle but that's what the case was. Pujara eventually fell, 4th time to Leach. The Indian skipper did not last long and went for yet another duck in the series. Rahane arrived and played a few delightful strokes and was looking really good before Anderson returned to send him packing at the stroke of Lunch.

What a finish to the session!. In the last 30 minutes or so in this session, ever since Rahane joined Rohit, the two Mumbai boys were scoring a bit freely but the ripper from Anderson in the last over before Lunch means England take the honors of the session.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anderson gives England their third wicket of the session and ensures that the lunch is a lot tastier for the tourists. 6th time Anderson has got the better of Rahane in Tests. A very good catch from Stokes at second slip as well.  There was swing on offer and that is why Anderson was brought into the attack before Lunch. The veteran pacer does the job for his skipper and his side. Anderson pulls his length back and bowls it in the channel of uncertainty around off. Rahane is committed to his defense. The ball though shapes away and takes the outside edge. It goes dropping to the left of second slip. Ben Stokes, there dives and takes a very fine catch. That will be LUNCH on Day 2!
Fullish around off, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends.
Length delivery on off, there is some little late inswing on this one. Rahane taps it to the on side and looks to sneak in a single. Rohit though is in no mood to take any unnecessary risk.
Down the leg side. Rahane looks to flick but misses. Foakes dives to his left and takes a good take.
Good length ball around off, Rahane defends it.
On the pads, Rahane flicks it to the on side and keeps the strike. Looks like we can sneak in another over before Lunch.

FOUR! Easy pickings! Bess decides to be generous and gift wraps a boundary to Rahane. A loopy full toss on off, Rahane is happy for the early summer gift from Bess. He has no problems driving this through extra cover for a boundary. That is the problem with Bess. He keeps things tight for 4 balls and then gives away such freebies.
Short and turning in. Rahane dabs it onto the ground in front of Pope at short leg.
Floated on leg, it is fuller as well. Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Short on leg, Rahane goes on his back foot and defends it onto the ground to the leg side.
Short on middle and leg. Rohit flicks it to the leg side. The ball bounces in front of Pope at short leg. It hits Pope and goes behind. The batters take a single.
In the air but safe! Fuller around off, this one shapes back in to the right-hander. Rahane chips his flick but gets enough to send it over and away from short mid-wicket fielder. Two taken.
Full around off, Rahane pushes it right of the meat to the left of mid off. Lawrence there slides and saves runs.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Good running! On the pads, Rahane flicks it through backward square leg. The fielder from fine leg has to make some ground to his left. Rahane sees it and calls for two and gets it with ease.
Full on off and middle, Rahane defends it with a straight bat.

Anderson comes and straightaway gets the swing. Beauty of a delivery! Too good for Rahane. Full, pitching in the channel of uncertainty around off. Rahane commits on his front foot. The ball though shapes away and beats the outside edge of Rahane's willow.
Change in bowling! James Anderson is back for a burst before the Lunch break.
Turn and bounce on this one. It is pitched on leg and turns away with some extra bounce. Rohit looks to flick but retracts. Foakes gets his gloves on it but cannot hold onto it.

FOUR! Rohit takes the risk but commits himself! The ball bounces just inside the ropes. Floated on off, Rohit gets down on his knee and slog sweeps it. There are two fielders in the deep on the leg side. Rohit hits it right between them. The ball bounces just inside the ropes.
Bess gives this one some air. Rohit defends it.
Good work from Pope at short leg. Floated on middle, Rohit turns it to the left of short leg. Pope dives, gets his hands to it, and saves runs for his side.
An off-break on middle and off. Rohit turns it with the spin to square leg.
Bess starts with a fuller delivery on middle and off. Rohit taps it back to the bowler.
Big Ben gets the much-needed break after bowling an extended spell. Here's Dom Bess with the ball now.
Another whip but this time along the ground and straight to the fielder. Floated on off, Rahane whips it but finds Sibley at short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, AR keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Rahane blocks it.
Rahane smartly goes back to defending as Leach tosses this up on middle.

FOUR! WHIPPED! Short and turning away. Rahane takes the risk of playing it against the spin. He whips it uppishly to the right of short mid-wicket. The fielder there dives but cannot get there and the ball races away to the fence.
Floated on middle and off, Rahane lunges forward and blocks it.

Uppish but safe! Good effort from Stokes. Bowls a full ball and manages to get some inward swing as well. Rohit looks to push but the ball hits the inner half of his bat and goes uppishly to the right of Stokes. He dives but cannot get there.
A little zip off the surface for STokes. This is on a length and bounces a tad more. Rahane manages to tickle it behind square leg for one.
Length ball outside off, asking Rahane to go for the drive. The Indian Test vice-captain is happy to eave it alone.
Rahane looks in the mood! Length delivery on off, Rahane pulls it over mid-wicket and gets a brace as Pope cleans it up before the ropes.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! Absolutely high-class from Rahane. Stokes dishes a full ball outside off. It is over pitched and away from the stump. Rahane is quick to lash onto it as he drives it magnificently through extra cover for a boundary.
On the stumps, Rohit keeps it out.
Floated on off, Rohit blocks it.
Flighted on off, Rahane drives it to the right of short extra cover. The fielder there dives and keeps it down to one.

FOUR! First boundary for Rahane! A loose delivery from Leach and he gets punished! A rare poor ball from Jack. He goes short on off, Rahane pulls it with power and timing through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slightly short and turning away. Rohit opens the face of the bat and runs it down away from slip for one. Brings up the 50  for India.
Flighted on middle and off, Rohit defends it.
Good length ball shaping away from around off. Rahane taps it to point and shouts a loud no.
Down the leg side. Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Full and wide outside off, Rahane lets it be.
The physio is out now to have quick concussion test on Rohit and also the helmet will be replaced. Good thing is Rohit is smiling so looks fine.

Ouch! That is off the helmet. A sharp bouncer from Stokes once again. Rohit goes for the pull but he is a bit too early. Gets hit on the helmet and the ball goes to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye. Rohit looks fine as he flashes a smile as the umpire calls for the physio.
Fuller and wider outside off. Left alone.
Shortish and on middle and leg, Rahane clips it to deep square leg and gets to the other end.
Floated on the stumps, Rohit keeps it out.

Bounce! Extra bounce but very well kept. Short around off, Rohit gets on his back foot to play but there is a tennis ball bounce on this. Rohit sways away from it looking at the bounce and loses his balance as well. Foakes does really well to gather the ball. He is also quick to take off the bails as Rohit was struggling for balance but Sharma never went out of the crease.
Straighter one just outside off. Rohit leaves it alone. Good leave as that one was not far away from the stump.
Short around off, Rohit taps it behind point and asks for a run. Rahane turns it down.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Tossed up around off, Rohit comes down the track and goes inside out over extra cover for a boundary. Just the third boundary in 88 balls for Rohit. Not very often that you see that.
Rohit comes down the track and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the pad. There is a stifled appeal from the visitors but nothing from the umpire.
Classical defense! Full around off, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends it textbook style to see off the over.
Stokes hits the deck hard, Rahane taps it onto the ground.
Full and wide outside off. There is some movement as Ben tries to tempt Jinks to drive. Rahane is calm as a cucumber and leaves it alone.
Stokes continues to pepper Rahane with the short stuff. Rahane once again is happy to tap it to the right of gully.
Shortish ball around off, Rahane taps it to the right of gully.
Back of a length ball around off, Rahane taps it to point and comes out for a run. Rohit though is quick to tell Rahane to turn his bike.
Floated around middle, kept out.
Rahane is up and running. Flat and just outside off, punched on the off side for a single.
Around off, Rahane defends.
Flat and around off, played back to the bowler.
Floated around off, kept out.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Rohit drills the drive to sweeper cover for one.
Full and around off, kept out by Rahane. End of a successful over from Stokes.
Good length and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Ajinkya Rahane, the deputy to Kohli strides out to the middle.

OUT! TAKEN! Stokes strikes and the Indian skipper has been sent packing for a duck. The crowd has gone silent here. Terrific bowling from Stokes. He kept coming at the batters and in his long extended spell, he has got the big fish. He runs in and bowls it short. It is outside off, Kohli is probably looking to get off the mark. Kohli hops and looks to poke it on the off side and get off the mark. He ends up getting a faint outside edge to the keeper. Foakes makes no mistake. Kohli looks shocked as he stands his ground. The extra bounce did the Indian skipper there. Massive, massive wicket for England here. Two big wickets in the session for the visitors.
Good length and around middle, keeping a bit low. Kohli does well to block it on the leg side.
Back of a length and around middle, pulled to deep square for one.
Fuller and wide outside off, driven to backward point. Wasn't off the middle of the willow.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Kohli blocks it back to Leach.
Full and wide outside off, pushed towards the cover region. Wanted a single but opted against it.
Floated and around off, kept out.
On middle, kept out.
Shortish and just outside off, punched to the man at covers.
And again! Too wide and outside off. Left alone by Rohit.
Another leave as this one is served wide outside off.
Close leave! This one came back in sharply after pitching outside off. Rohit covers his stumps and makes a leave.
